are likely to be a force to be reckoned with again in Paris.\", \"from\": 307, \"to\": 489, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 396, \"end\": 410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999926104, \"rank\": 7.391604644942e-12, \"text\": \"Tokyo Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 483, \"end\": 488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999992231908725, \"rank\": 7.768097639815134e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both are four-time world champions, and Hifumi Abe told reporters in Tokyo on Tuesday that he does not want to be outdone by his younger sister this summer.\", \"from\": 491, \"to\": 647, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 531, \"end\": 541, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hifumi_Abe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hifumi Abe\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hifumi_Abe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hifumi_Abe\"}, {\"begin\": 560, \"end\": 565, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.5702697150965758, \"rank\": 0.7535561166375057, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I know we are both working hard and we share the same target - that fact alone helps me,\\\" said the 26-year-old.\", \"from\": 649, \"to\": 761, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When I see her working hard and putting in the effort, it gives me strength and makes me think that I have to work hard too.\\\"\", \"from\": 763, \"to\": 889, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hifumi beat Georgia's Vazha Margvelashvili to win the men's under-66kg Olympic title in Tokyo shortly after Uta claimed the women's under-52kg gold beating France's Amandine Buchard.\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 1073, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 903, \"end\": 910, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9504533182452806, \"rank\": 0.05105800092402327, \"text\": \"Georgia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 913, \"end\": 933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vazha_Margvelashvili\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Vazha Margvelashvili\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vazha_Margvelashvili\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vazha_Margvelashvili\"}, {\"begin\": 979, \"end\": 984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.5702697150965758, \"rank\": 0.7535561166375057, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1047, \"end\": 1053, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.6443921579405752, \"rank\": 0.34180133996482803, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1056, \"end\": 1072, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amandine_Buchard\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Amandine Buchard\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amandine_Buchard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amandine_Buchard\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The siblings will again compete on the same day in Paris, and Uta said they will keep an eye on each other's matches.\", \"from\": 1075, \"to\": 1192, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1126, \"end\": 1131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999992231908725, \"rank\": 7.768097639815134e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If we both progress through the tournament then that helps support each other,\\\" said the 23-year-old.\", \"from\": 1194, \"to\": 1296, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The most important thing is to keep winning so that we can both reach the final and win.\\\"\", \"from\": 1298, \"to\": 1388, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Abe siblings followed up their Olympic success by winning world titles in their respective weight classes in 2022 and 2023.\", \"from\": 1390, \"to\": 1517, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1394, \"end\": 1397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shinzo_Abe\", \"score\": 0.9999877276753062, \"rank\": 1.224043636323885e-05, \"text\": \"Abe\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shinzo_Abe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shinzo_Abe\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hifumi said competing at an Olympics away from home for the first time is likely to be his biggest challenge.\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1628, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There will be a time difference, so I have to make sure I prepare myself right to be in good shape,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1630, \"to\": 1740, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"With the judo side of it, as long as I prepare myself as I normally do, I am confident there is no way I will lose.\\\"\", \"from\": 1742, \"to\": 1859, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Al Jazeera English:\", \"from\": 1879, \"to\": 1905, \"entities\": []}]}"